-- India's Piramal, Dutch APG join hands for $1 bln India infra investment
-- By Sumeet Chatterjee and Devidutta Tripathy
-- Tue Jul 29, 2014 11:15PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 30 (Reuters) - India's Piramal Enterprises Ltd <PIRA.NS> has tied up with Dutch pension fund APG Asset Management to invest in rupee-denominated mezzanine instruments issued by Indian infrastructure companies, the two sides said on Wednesday.

